@Oikofuge 

That is so sad!  "Go Fish" was my first card game--vividly-recalling, exciting experience!--and I couldn't remember the word for "8"--so I asked for "Eyeglasses."  I was crushed by the hilarious laughter ....  
Decades later, I decided to teach this game to my (multi-handicapped) class, which included some aides.  None of them, including the adults, had ever played it!  It was a great teaching tool-- taking turns, paying attention, remembering--and everyone loved it.  Much hilarity when The Teacher forgot who had asked for what...  The aides came back the next week saying, "I taught my whole family!  We played it all weekend!"  Go Fish became the reward at the end of a good day...  Fun for all ages!

